      },
      "source": [
        "# 🤖 NLP Assignment – Task 3: Chatbot using Hugging Face Transformers\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objective\n",
        "Build a console-based conversational chatbot using the **DialoGPT** pre-trained transformer model from Hugging Face. The chatbot dynamically generates responses and maintains multi-turn conversation context.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Pipeline Flow\n",
        "```\n",
        "User Input → Tokenization → Model Processing → Response Generation → Display Output → Loop Until Exit\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5jtoyOLLhD3l"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Step 1: Install Required Libraries\n",
        "\n",
        "We install the `transformers` and `torch` libraries needed to load and run the pre-trained model."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_lZvB_HWhHb_"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Install Hugging Face Transformers and PyTorch (if not already installed)\n",
        "!pip install transformers torch"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UX-rro0mhLKc"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Step 2: Import Libraries\n",
        "\n",
        "We import the necessary modules:\n",
        "- `AutoModelForCausalLM` – loads the pre-trained causal language model (DialoGPT)\n",
        "- `AutoTokenizer` – converts text to token IDs the model understands\n",
        "- `torch` – PyTorch backend for tensor operations"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Iv1wdp7HhWcS",
        "outputId": "438bef66-b1bd-4c61-e7eb-0c5ca5aa7584"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Import required libraries\n",
        "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Libraries imported successfully.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nJgceNCGhbNw"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Step 3: Load Pre-Trained Model and Tokenizer\n",
        "\n",
        "In this step, we load the pre-trained **DialoGPT-medium** model and its corresponding tokenizer from Hugging Face.\n",
        "\n",
        "DialoGPT is a dialogue-focused version of GPT-2, fine-tuned on conversational data, making it suitable for chatbot applications.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Components:\n",
        "- **Tokenizer**: Converts input text into token IDs that the model can understand  \n",
        "- **Model**: Generates responses based on the input tokens and conversation context  "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 259,
          "referenced_widgets": [
            "2b45de92de734a7694a211f42b63480a",
            "3900c4533fe34d369f992a6aeb919422",
            "753f9e915ca945bc9f85641064413748",
            "b0732737e6e94246a651159ee51f1d5f",
            "6913983d7cf94929a419c127a89821b7",
            "c34a80c6a5504aa39900b4893c35f52c",
            "34deb21794e843a29548a4409e40c0f1",
            "718f3cc1f3aa4ebc81864ab1dc6867e0",
            "006371f1c0844039b235a4599d95b906",
            "5169003bb727472489e0665d5411175d",
            "024abb7e36c748f8b819d6e2d9647ae7"
          ]
        },
        "id": "wbkwTDr-hgQP",
        "outputId": "fd7140c7-6097-4723-ede2-f5555f477132"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "MODEL_NAME = \"microsoft/DialoGPT-large\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Loading model...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\n",
        "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Model loaded successfully!\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ohdYElxohkNv"
      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "## Step 4: Define the Response Generation Function\n",
        "\n",
        "This function generates chatbot responses based on user input and conversation history.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Functionality:\n",
        "- Encodes the user input into tokens  \n",
        "- Maintains conversation history for context  \n",
        "- Passes input to the model for response generation  \n",
        "- Applies parameters like `top_k`, `top_p`, and `temperature` for better output  \n",
        "- Decodes the generated tokens into readable text  \n",
        "- Returns both the response and updated conversation history  "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "CZiR95tahp99",
        "outputId": "67d992e5-b0af-4cba-a311-526db2a2bda4"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def generate_response(user_input, chat_history_ids):\n",
        "    \n",
        "    new_input_ids = tokenizer.encode(\n",
        "    \"User: \" + user_input + \"\\nBot:  Give a clear and complete answer:\",\n",
        "    return_tensors='pt'\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "    bot_input_ids = torch.cat(\n",
        "        [chat_history_ids, new_input_ids], dim=-1\n",
        "    ) if chat_history_ids is not None else new_input_ids\n",
        "\n",
        "    chat_history_ids = model.generate(\n",
        "        bot_input_ids,\n",
        "        max_new_tokens=50,\n",
        "        pad_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n",
        "        attention_mask=torch.ones_like(bot_input_ids),\n",
        "        do_sample=True,\n",
        "        top_k=50,\n",
        "        top_p=0.95,\n",
        "        temperature=0.7,\n",
        "        repetition_penalty=1.2\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    response = tokenizer.decode(\n",
        "        chat_history_ids[:, bot_input_ids.shape[-1]:][0],\n",
        "        skip_special_tokens=True\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    return response, chat_history_ids"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "fJDRDbgQh5nP",
        "outputId": "80918e79-986a-4dd9-c816-26fe86b546e4"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def run_chatbot():\n",
        "    chat_history_ids = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"🤖 Chatbot ready! Enter your message below (type 'exit' to stop)\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        user_input = input() \n",
        "\n",
        "        if user_input.lower() in [\"exit\", \"quit\"]:\n",
        "            print(\"Chatbot: Goodbye! 👋\")\n",
        "            break\n",
        "\n",
        "        new_input_ids = tokenizer.encode(\n",
        "            \"User: \" + user_input + \"\\nBot:\",\n",
        "            return_tensors='pt'\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "        bot_input_ids = torch.cat(\n",
        "            [chat_history_ids, new_input_ids],\n",
        "            dim=-1\n",
        "        ) if chat_history_ids is not None else new_input_ids\n",
        "\n",
        "        chat_history_ids = model.generate(\n",
        "            bot_input_ids,\n",
        "            max_new_tokens=50,\n",
        "            pad_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n",
        "            do_sample=True,\n",
        "            top_k=40,\n",
        "            top_p=0.9,\n",
        "            temperature=0.6,\n",
        "            repetition_penalty=1.2\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "        # LIMIT HISTORY SIZE\n",
        "        if chat_history_ids.shape[-1] > 800:\n",
        "            chat_history_ids = chat_history_ids[:, -800:]\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(\"\\nYou:\", user_input)\n",
        "        print(\"Chatbot:\", response)\n",
        "        print()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "X9PDUsTth9FZ"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Step 6: Sample Chatbot Interaction Output\n",
        "\n",
        "Below is a simulated demo of the chatbot interaction (for reference, as `input()` does not execute in static view):"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fl5u-jyMiCE9"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "run_chatbot()"
      ]
    },
